        <td bgcolor='black' valign='top' width='100%'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> Egyptians were the first necromancers in  the History of the world. How do I know this, its easy, for everyday that they lived, they prepared for death and built their entire civilization upon this one small part of life, the end. Why? What was the logic behind this? Its too bad we dont know, If I had a time machine, I would go there to find out. Its amazing how one class in EQ is related to a race of humans that has vanished and left great monuments  of bearing that we still look up to this day. It seems that death is life. Why do we live? So we can die no? Are you not dying now? Funny how some of this works, as I have "grown up" from the first post I made, I have had my eyes open further into how this world works. I remember one of my first posts. It was a stupid rant/flame and I made a troll of myself over something I knew nothing about. Now I seek the truth and stay within the shadows untill I am ready to express my thoughts and views to others. I want to thank you all for helping me "advance" my thinking process. It helps people to mature into logical and respectfull people. This board has had the biggest impact on me since I was in the Navy. When I was there, my friend taught me something that I can never forget. He told me, "When you learn to learn, then you will understand without knowing..." Well dark brethren, I have learned to learn again and I just thought that you all should understand that it is greatly appreciated. With reason, understanding, and respect, we have come a long way from other boards. If you go there, most people flame and rant to/at others in the same way I did when I first came here. Now I am different. I write this so that you all can see how I do, the light has to have darkness so that it can be called light. Life works in the same way here. Just a few thoughts from ME, not Velous. Once again, I thank you all for your moral support and your logical thinking. If more people did that, then the world would be a better place.</P><P>always thinking...(processing)...<BR>Velous</P><P>"I don't talk to dead people; I make them scream."</P><P>"I make dead people."</font></td>
